"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody, out here in Neadville, Texas, I want to talk about what we're trying to do with the land here. We're trying to reinvigorate the life into it. A lot of times with dead compacted land like this, our soil, is that you see that it hasn't the life in it, the microbes and the earthworms and the crickets and all the other things that come with good healthy soil. And what we're trying to do is reinvigorate that because that will fluff it up in a manner of speaking. It'll create pockets where moisture can get absorbed more readily, where roots will have an easier time going into it. And on top of that, the roots really respond well to fungal and microbial activity. They're integral in uh developing these systems. So what we're trying to do is trying to reinvigorate the life into that, and what we'll how we'll do that is we'll take living good compost and we'll add it on top and then let roots and earthworms and other things dig into the dead soil and incorporate that into the living soil and do this without tilling. Thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody, out here in Neadville, Texas, I want to talk about what we're trying to do with the land here.\",\n      \"start\": 1.28,\n      \"end\": 6.16,\n      \"duration\": 4.88,\n      \"confidence\": 0.99,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.68,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.76,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.92,\n          \"end\": 2.0,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confi